President Muhammadu Buhari has sent a delegation led by his Chief of Staff, Abba Kyari, to deliver his condolence messages to Governor Abdullahi Ganduje and the Emir of Kano, Muhammadu Sanusi II over the death of Dan Iyan Kano, Ambassador Ado Sanusi. The delegation was made up of the Minister of Defence, Maj.-General Bashir Magashi,  Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Alhaji Sabo Nanono, Permanent Secretary, State House, Jalal Arabi, Senior Special Assistants to the President, Sarki Abba and Garba Shehu and the State Chief of Protocol, Ambassador Lawal Kazaure. President Buhari, in separate letters to the Governor and the Emir, said that he was shocked to learn about the death of the Ambassador. “I received the sad news of the death of Ambassador Ado Sanusi, an astute career diplomat. Sanusi was a dedicated public servant who served very creditably as Nigeria’s Foreign Service Officer. He was a conscientious, competent, distinguished, patriotic and remarkable diplomat who served his country and immediate community with distinction,” the President said in a statement issued yesterday by his media aide, Garba Shehu. Governor Ganduje, who thanked the President for sending the delegation, assured him of support and loyalty on behalf of the people of the state. The Emir, while receiving the delegation, also thanked the President for supporting the treatment of the late Ambassador before he died.  Buhari sends delegation to Ganduje, Sanusi over Dan Iyan Kano's death Buhari commiserates with Emir Sanusi over uncle's death Ciroman Kano: The Road Not Taken by Sanusi Bayero